<main>
	<!-- Hero Section -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-primary text-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 font-heading">HVAC INSTALLATION</h1>
				<p class="text-xl mb-8">Upgrade to better efficiency &amp; performance in Bell County &amp; the central Texas
					area.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Service Overview -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
				<div>
					<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
						<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent mr-4"></div>
						<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary font-heading">PROFESSIONAL HVAC INSTALLATION SERVICES IN
							KILLEEN</h2>
					</div>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						Alltek Services offers a wide variety of options for HVAC installation in Killeen and the surrounding areas.
						We have more than 30 years of experience in the HVAC industry and extensive product knowledge.
					</p>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-8">
						Our highly qualified technicians will provide honest, trustworthy advice and install your new equipment for
						optimal performance. We stand behind our installations with a two-year labor warranty.
					</p>
					<a
						href="/contact"
						class="inline-block bg-secondary hover:bg-secondary/90 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-md transition-colors"
					>
						Get Free Estimate
					</a>
				</div>

				<div>
					<img
						src="/images-optimized/hvac_technician_600w.webp"
						alt="Certified HVAC technician inspecting a heating and air conditioning system in Belton, TX"
						class="rounded-lg shadow-xl w-full h-auto object-cover"
						width="600"
						height="400"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Services List -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-lightgray">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="text-center mb-12">
				<div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent mr-4"></div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary font-heading">UNDERSTANDING YOUR HVAC SYSTEM'S LIFESPAN</h2>
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent ml-4"></div>
				</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-left text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto">
					The expected lifespan of an HVAC system can vary depending on several factors, including the type of system,
					how well it’s maintained, and the quality of the installation.
				</p>

			</div>
			<div class="text-left mb-12 m-7">
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto">
					<strong>On average, you can expect the following lifespans for different types of HVAC systems:</strong>
				</p>
				<ul class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-4">
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Furnaces</strong>: A well-maintained gas or electric furnace typically lasts between
						15 to 20 years. High-efficiency models may have a slightly shorter lifespan due to the increased stress on
						their
						components.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Air Conditioners</strong>: Central air conditioning units typically have a lifespan
						of 15 to 20 years. Like furnaces, proper maintenance and usage can extend their lifespan.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Heat Pumps</strong>: Heat pumps, which can provide both heating and cooling, have a
						similar lifespan of 15 to 20 years.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Ductless Mini-Split Systems</strong>: These systems often last 15 to 20 years or more
						with proper care.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Geothermal Heat Pumps</strong>: Geothermal systems are known for their longevity and
						can last 20 to 25 years for the indoor components and 25 to 50 years or more for the ground loop system.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-7">
					It’s important to note that these are average lifespans, and individual cases may vary.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-4">
					<strong>Several factors can affect the lifespan of an HVAC system:</strong>
				</p>
				<ul class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-4">
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Maintenance</strong>: Regular maintenance, including cleaning, filter replacement,
						and professional inspections, can significantly extend the life of your HVAC system.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Quality of Installation</strong>: Proper installation by qualified professionals is
						crucial. Poor installation can lead to premature system failure.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Usage Patterns</strong>: The frequency and intensity of system use can impact its
						longevity.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Climate</strong>: HVAC systems in areas with extreme temperature variations or high
						humidity may experience more stress and wear.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Brand and Model</strong>: Higher-quality and more energy-efficient systems often have
						longer lifespans.
					</li>
					<li class="mb-4"><strong>Technological Advancements</strong>: Newer systems may be more energy-efficient and
						have advanced features, which could influence decisions to replace older systems.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="py-8 md:py-12 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="text-center mb-12">
				<div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent mr-4"></div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary font-heading uppercase">Extend Your HVAC System's Life with Expert
						Maintenance</h2>
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent ml-4"></div>
				</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-left  max-w-3xl mx-auto">
					While the expected lifespan of an HVAC system can vary depending on factors such as usage, maintenance, and
					environmental conditions, there are steps you can take to maximize the lifespan of your system. Our Belton
					HVAC experts can provide tips and recommendations to help ensure your HVAC system operates efficiently and
					lasts for years to come.
				</p>

			</div>
			<div class="text-left mb-12 m-7">
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto">
					<strong>Ways to maximize the lifespan of your HVAC system include:</strong>
				</p>
				<ul class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-4">
					<li class="mb-4">Regular maintenance and tune-ups</li>
					<li class="mb-4">Changing air filters regularly</li>
					<li class="mb-4">Keeping the outdoor unit clear of debris</li>
					<li class="mb-4">Monitoring and maintaining proper refrigerant levels</li>
					<li class="mb-4">Sealing and insulating ductwork</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-7">
					By taking proactive steps to care for your HVAC system, you can extend its lifespan, reduce the need for
					costly repairs, and ensure consistent comfort in your home.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-4">
					When your HVAC system reaches the end of its expected lifespan, it’s generally a good idea to consider
					replacing it, as older systems tend to be less energy-efficient and can become costly to maintain.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-4">
					Regular maintenance and prompt repairs can help extend the life of your HVAC system and keep it running
					efficiently.
				</p>

			</div>

		</div>
	</section>

